On android, you may need some folder to no being indexed. It could be photos or videos&hellip;
To do so, use a ES Explorer for example and a &lsquo;.nomedia&rsquo; file inside the desired folder.
No index will be done in that folder. I like to do it when I temporary add TV series and don&rsquo;t want them to be indexed. By this way I don&rsquo;t see them in the Gallery application for example.
